{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timevalref\/toiso8601()"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeValRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeValRef\/TimeValProtocol-Implementations"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeValRef\/toIso8601()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"toIso8601","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ISO 8601 allows a large number of date\/time formats, with or without"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"punctuation and optional elements. The format returned by this function","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is a complete date and time, with optional punctuation included, the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"UTC time zone represented as “Z”, and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"tv_usec"},{"type":"text","text":" part included if"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and only if it is nonzero, i.e. either"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"“YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ” or “YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.fffffZ”."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This corresponds to the Internet date\/time format defined by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.ietf.org\/rfc\/rfc3339.txt","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and to either of the two most-precise formats defined by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the W3C Note","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/NOTE-datetime-19980827"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Both of these documents are profiles of ISO 8601.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_format()"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"g_strdup_printf()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if a different","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"variation of ISO 8601 format is required."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"time"},{"type":"text","text":" represents a date which is too large to fit into a "},{"code":"struct tm","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned. This is platform dependent. Note also that since"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"GTimeVal","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" stores the number of seconds as a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"glong"},{"type":"text","text":", on 32-bit systems it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is subject to the year 2038 problem. Accordingly, since GLib 2.62, this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function has been deprecated. Equivalent functionality is available using:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["GDateTime *dt = g_date_time_new_from_unix_utc (time_val);","iso8601_string = g_date_time_format_iso8601 (dt);","g_date_time_unref (dt);"],"syntax":null},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The return value of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_time_val_to_iso8601()"},{"type":"text","text":" has been nullable since GLib"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"2.54; before then, GLib would crash under the same conditions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"to_iso8601 is deprecated:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"#GTimeVal is not year-2038-safe. Use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"g_date_time_format_iso8601(dt) instead.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","platforms":[],"externalID":"s:4GLib15TimeValProtocolPAAE9toIso8601SSSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib10TimeValRefV","extendedModule":"GLib","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"toIso8601","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"toIso8601()","symbolKind":"method"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Converts ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"time"},{"text":" into an RFC 3339 encoded string, relative to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). This is one of the many formats","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"allowed by ISO 8601."}],"references":{"http://www.w3.org/TR/NOTE-datetime-19980827":{"identifier":"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/NOTE-datetime-19980827","type":"link","title":"Date and Time Formats","url":"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/NOTE-datetime-19980827","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Date and Time Formats"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeValRef":{"abstract":[{"text":"Represents a precise time, with seconds and microseconds.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TimeValRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timevalref","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeValRef","role":"symbol","title":"TimeValRef","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":